 "faq": [
  {
   "question": "Where does Retribution Paladin Phase 1 BiS come from?",
   "answer": "From the gear worn by 333 top-ranked Retribution Paladin DPS parses on Warcraft Logs during Phase 1 (Karazhan, Gruul's Lair and Magtheridon), aggregated per slot — what high parsers actually equip, not a spreadsheet ideal."
  },
  {
   "question": "What are the highest-consensus Retribution Paladin items in Phase 1?",
   "answer": "Libram of Avengement (86%), Lionheart Champion (81%), Justicar Crown (79%). When an item sits above ~70% among top parsers, treat it as the priority drop to chase."
  },
  {
   "question": "Should I follow this list exactly for Phase 1?",
   "answer": "Use it as a loot-priority guide, not a checklist — expand each slot's alternatives, because second-choice items are often within a few percent and drop from entirely different bosses in Karazhan, Gruul's Lair and Magtheridon."
  },
  {
   "question": "What gems should a Retribution Paladin use in Phase 1?",
   "answer": "Relentless Earthstorm Diamond in the meta socket, then Bold Living Ruby, Sovereign Nightseye and Rigid Dawnstone in the coloured sockets. Epic gems only arrive with patch 2.4 (Sunwell), so these rare-quality cuts are the ceiling for this phase."
  },
  {
   "question": "What enchants does a Retribution Paladin need in Phase 1?",
   "answer": "10 slots are worth enchanting. The biggest swings are Glyph of Ferocity on head, Greater Inscription of Vengeance on shoulders, Nethercobra Leg Armor on legs and Enchant Weapon - Mongoose on main hand. The head and shoulder enchants are consumable items rather than enchanter work — Glyph of Ferocity comes from Fedryen Swiftwpear — Zangarmarsh."
  }
 ]
